About Udemy
Udemy has helped more than 30 million people learn with its online courses. Thanks to the company's self-paced lessons, studying new topics and brushing up on what you already know is more convenient than traditional models of education. Udemy offers over 100,000 courses, spanning a wide range of topics. You'll find coursework on IT, design, marketing, personal development and much more. The company has options for individual study as well as plans for businesses. For example, companies like Pinterest, Adidas and Lyft take advantage of Udemy's online courses for their employees. Along with its education platform, Udemy has an app for students to use on the go. You can’t put a price on a good education, but you can score some pretty amazing online discounts on it. Many courses are inexpensive considering the value of the course material, and sometimes you can even find a deal on one that is typically expensive. Udemy and some of the instructors who teach on the platform distribute online promo codes, coupon codes and other discount codes that can help you save on your next course.

Udemy Discount Tips

Udemy Discount Tips   

Udemy sometimes runs promotions with steep discounts on its classes, starting as low as $12.99 each. With some of these courses originally costing more than $100, that means big savings. Whenever possible, look for Udemy promo codes and online coupons that will knock a few bucks off of your total. Even when you can’t find a coupon code that applies to your order, you can still take advantage of online deals by joining the company’s email list and keeping an eye on the deals displayed on the front page.  

This site does not offer status-based discounts like a student discount, senior citizen discount or military discount. If you’re trying to get a good deal every time you take a Udemy course, check out these savings tips.

Finding and Using Udemy Coupons  

Look for offers on the website. The company sometimes displays current discounts on the banner on top of the home page. Many of Udemy's offers are limited-time deals, so act fast. When you click on a discounted course, look for red text under the price—that's the amount of time left to get that deal.

When you’ve found a course that you’re interested in and you’re ready to check out, click on the shopping cart at the top right of the website. Enter your promo code in the box under your shopping cart's red checkout button and hit Apply. When you go to your cart, you may notice that a coupon has already been applied. That happens when the course you added is already discounted, because the website automatically applies these Udemy discount codes. This site does not have stackable coupons, so choose your discount codes carefully.

Subscribe to the Udemy Email Program 

Once you’ve created an account on the site, enabling email updates is a good idea. By doing so, you will receive Udemy deals, updates and tailored course recommendations straight to your inbox. If you sign up to teach online courses, you'll get specific deals and tips just for teachers.

Udemy does not offer a rewards program or a loyalty program. Joining the email list is the best way to stay in touch with the company and rest assured knowing that you will hear about all of the exciting deals and promos the site has to offer.

Udemy Return Policy  

Sometimes, you may realize that the course you purchased is not right for you. If this happens, you can return your course within 30 days of purchasing it. The one exception to this rule: if you have downloaded all of the course material, you can no longer return it. In some cases, you might receive your refund in the form of Udemy credits, rather than on your credit card or other original method of payment. This depends on the type of course that you are enrolled in.

Udemy Price Adjustment Policy 

It can be very frustrating to purchase a course, just to receive a coupon code days later that could have discounted your purchase. Luckily, Udemy will issue a price adjustment on any course that drops in price or becomes eligible for a discount. All you have to do is request a price adjustment from the company’s support team within 30 days of your initial purchase.

Get the Best Shipping Price

You don’t need to worry about finding a free shipping promo code, as all of Udemy’s services are rendered over the internet. 

Contact Udemy Customer Service

Have questions about your recent Udemy purchase, a price adjustment or anything else? You can get in touch with the company by visiting their Contact Us page, which offers a robust supply of FAQs and helpful information.
